I can't see my campaigns anymore

I'm sorry to hear that you're having trouble seeing your campaigns. Could you please provide more details? For example, did you recently make any changes to your account or settings? This will help me assist you better.
The campaigns that should be visible in the dash, arn't

Thanks for the additional information. Let's try a few steps to resolve this issue. First, please check if you are logged into the correct ad account and organization. You can manage multiple ad accounts under one organization, so it's possible that you might be in a different account or organization than where your campaigns are located. Here's how you can check and switch between accounts and organizations: [Account Management Guide](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/17539290349709-Account-Management-Guide). If you're still having trouble, please let me know!
I'm here to help with whatever you need! Let me know your question, and I'll do my best to assist you right away.

I understand you'd like to chat with an agent. Unfortunately, live chat support isn't available at the moment. However, you can email our support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance. Please include details about your issue so they can help you more effectively.

I'm sorry to hear that your audiences are missing as well. This could be related to the same issue with your campaigns not being visible. Please make sure you are logged into the correct ad account and organization. If everything seems correct and you're still experiencing issues, I recommend reaching out to our support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance. They will be able to investigate this issue more thoroughly.
